    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="805"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.86/4–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 805<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Saudi Arabia (<persName corresp="#p_WG1"
                            type="from">Wadsworth</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-20T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 20, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>440. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 290, April 15.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d805fn1">Printed as telegram 407 to Amman, <ref target="#d796"
                            >Document 796</ref>.</note> From our listening post in this primitive
                    still basically puritanical Wahabi community in which St. John Philby tells me
                    Court thinking continues governed largely by old King’s theme that <gloss
                        target="#t_SA3">SA</gloss> is “firstly Moslem and only secondly Arab” we can
                    best answer question in referenced telegram by saying we see no procedure for
                    getting parties together for any purpose and question two by reporting that not
                    even our generally well informed Embassy Arab consultant has ever heard of
                        <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> or bothers even endeavor comprehend
                    details border machinery.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
